---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy — STR Host Tools"
  description="How STR Host Tools handles data: no tracking cookies, calculator inputs stay in your browser, email captures only when you opt in."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <article class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9 prose">
      <h1 class="text-h1 font-serif text-navy leading-tight">
        Privacy<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lead text-ink-2">
        Short version: we don't sell you, we don't surveil you, we don't pop modals at you.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        Calculator inputs never leave your browser. Every tool on this site runs client-side — your nightly rate, occupancy, cost numbers, and tax assumptions are computed locally and reflected in the URL so you can bookmark or share a scenario. No values are POSTed to a server.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you opt into a lead magnet (e.g., the STR Host Income Report PDF), your email address is sent to our email provider so we can deliver the file. We don't share that list with third parties. You can unsubscribe from any email we send.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies & analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics 4 with cross-domain attribution across the STR cluster (strhost.tools, thestrledger.com, strbuyers.tools, strops.tools, strguests.tools) so we can see whether the calculators feed paid-product interest. GA4 is the only third-party script on the site. We don't run advertising pixels, retargeting, or session-replay.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not use tracking cookies for marketing. Browser-level "Do Not Track" and Global Privacy Control signals are respected — if your browser sends them, GA4 events for your session are dropped.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>
        Some outbound links (notably to The STR Ledger product pages) are affiliate or attribution links. They don't change what you pay; they let us know which calculators feed which purchases.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about how your data is handled: use the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. We answer within a week.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose :global(h2) { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--t-h2-size); color: var(--brand-navy); margin-top: var(--sp-7); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.1; }
  .prose :global(p) { color: var(--fg-1); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.6; }
  .prose :global(a) { color: var(--brand-navy); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--brand-gold); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
